<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Bentley Flying Spur Guide</title>
  <style>
    /* General Styles */
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffa500, #90ee90); /* Orange and light green gradient */
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      color: #333; /* Dark grey text for contrast */
    }

    .container {
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 20px auto;
      padding: 20px;
      background: #ffffff; /* White background */
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.3); /* Orange shadow */
      border-radius: 10px;
    }

    h1, h2 {
      color: #ff8c00; /* Dark orange */
    }

    h1 {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
    }

    h2 {
      font-size: 1.8rem;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      border-bottom: 3px solid #90ee90; /* Light green */
      display: inline-block;
    }

    p, ul {
      line-height: 1.8;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: #555; /* Dark grey for readability */
    }

    ul {
      list-style-type: disc;
      padding-left: 20px;
    }

    li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    /* Card Styles */
    .card {
      background: #f9f9f9; /* Light grey */
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.2); /* Orange shadow */
      padding: 20px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    }

    .card:hover {
      transform: translateY(-5px);
      box-shadow: 0 8px 16px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.4); /* Brighter orange shadow on hover */
    }

    /* Images Section */
    .images {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }

    .images img {
      max-width: 60%;
      height: auto;
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.3); /* Orange shadow */
      transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .images img:hover {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    /* Video Section */
    .video-container {
      text-align: center;
      margin-top: 30px;
      padding: 20px;
      background: #f9f9f9; /* Light grey */
      border-radius: 10px;
      box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.3); /* Orange shadow */
      transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    }

    .video-container:hover {
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }

    .video-container iframe {
      max-width: 100%;
      height: 400px;
      border-radius: 10px;
      border: 5px solid #90ee90; /* Light green */
    }

    /* Responsive Design */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .images img {
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .video-container iframe {
        height: 250px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 2rem;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Bentley Flying Spur Guide</h1>

    <!-- Overview Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>The Bentley Flying Spur is the ultimate luxury sedan, combining breathtaking performance with exquisite craftsmanship. Known for its powerful engine, opulent interior, and cutting-edge technology, the Flying Spur is designed for those who demand the very best in both comfort and performance. It is a true representation of Bentley's commitment to excellence.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Single Image Section -->
    <div class="images">
      <img src="https://www.example.com/bentley-flying-spur.jpg" alt="Bentley Flying Spur Image">
    </div>

    <!-- Key Features Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Key Features</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Luxurious Interior:</strong> Handcrafted with premium leather, wood veneers, and metal accents.</li>
        <li><strong>Powerful Performance:</strong> Equipped with a 6.0-liter W12 engine producing 626 horsepower.</li>
        <li><strong>Advanced Technology:</strong> Features a state-of-the-art infotainment system and driver assistance systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Customization:</strong> Offers bespoke options to tailor the car to the owner's exact preferences.</li>
        <li><strong>Exclusivity:</strong> A symbol of status and refinement, reserved for the most discerning clients.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Performance Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Performance</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Engine:</strong> 6.0-liter twin-turbocharged W12 engine producing 626 horsepower and 664 lb-ft of torque.</li>
        <li><strong>Transmission:</strong> 8-speed dual-clutch automatic with all-wheel drive.</li>
        <li><strong>Acceleration:</strong> 0-60 mph in just 3.7 seconds.</li>
        <li><strong>Top Speed:</strong> 207 mph (333 km/h).</li>
        <li><strong>Weight:</strong> 5,379 lbs (2,440 kg), designed for stability and comfort.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Video Section -->
    <div class="video-container">
      <h2>Learn More About the Bentley Flying Spur</h2>
      <iframe
        width="560"
        height="400"
        src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/example-video-id" <!-- Replace with a relevant Bentley Flying Spur video -->
        title="YouTube video player"
        frameborder="0"
        allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture"
        allowfullscreen
      ></iframe>
    </div>

    <!-- Technology Section -->
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Technology</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Infotainment System:</strong> Features a large touchscreen, voice control, and a premium audio system.</li>
        <li><strong>Driver Assistance:</strong> Includes adaptive cruise control, night vision, and a 360-degree camera system.</li>
        <li><strong>Comfort Features:</strong> Equipped with massaging seats, advanced climate control, and ambient lighting.</li>
        <li><strong>Safety:</strong> Comprehensive safety features, including airbags, ABS, and stability control.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>